WEBVTT

00:06.639 --> 00:09.008
Alison:
Previously on <i>the affair...</i>

00:09.010 --> 00:11.677
- There was this girl working
here the last time we came.

00:11.679 --> 00:13.112
- I'll let her know
you stopped by.

00:13.114 --> 00:14.646
- Helen and I are trying
to raise

00:14.648 --> 00:18.217
Decent human beings--
not just get more, spend more.

00:18.219 --> 00:20.686
- As you accept our money
for private school tuition?

00:20.688 --> 00:23.255
- Mom, stop trying
to pick a fight with my husband.

00:23.257 --> 00:25.157
- I'm doing some research
for my book.

00:25.159 --> 00:27.092
- Well, how about a tour
of the island?

00:27.094 --> 00:30.562
This island is famous
for its old victorian hotels.

00:30.564 --> 00:33.298
I want to know what it feels
like to be underneath you.

00:33.300 --> 00:34.633
- I need a room, please.

00:34.635 --> 00:36.135
- Will that be cash or credit?

00:36.137 --> 00:37.403
- How much do you need?

00:37.405 --> 00:38.804
- What are you doing here?
- Oh, hey.

00:38.806 --> 00:40.773
- Oh, your girl's here.
- My girl?

00:40.775 --> 00:42.274
- Weren't you looking
for alison earlier?

00:42.276 --> 00:44.243
- No, I think you
must have misunderstood.

00:44.245 --> 00:45.377
- I'm sure I did.
- If I were you,

00:45.379 --> 00:46.779
I'd be talking to oscar hodges.

00:46.781 --> 00:48.380
There are feuds out here
that have been

00:48.382 --> 00:49.648
Going on for almost a century.

00:49.650 --> 00:51.383
- Between the hodges
and the lockharts?

00:51.385 --> 00:53.252
- You don't understand
this town, detective.

00:53.254 --> 00:54.720
- Who the fuck died and--

00:54.722 --> 00:56.588
- We may fight,
we may hurt each other.

00:56.590 --> 00:58.257
But we're like family here.

00:58.259 --> 01:00.592
- You care about me, bailey,
because we go way back.

01:00.594 --> 01:03.262
And because you understand
that people need to change

01:03.264 --> 01:04.530
In order to survive.

01:04.532 --> 01:05.798
- Here it is.

01:05.800 --> 01:07.800
That's him.
- Your grandfather?

01:07.802 --> 01:09.601
- He raised me.

01:09.603 --> 01:11.603
They say this beach is haunted.

01:11.605 --> 01:13.806
- Seems like such
a pleasant place.

01:13.808 --> 01:16.275
- I had a son.

01:16.277 --> 01:18.310
He drowned.
- When?

01:18.312 --> 01:20.679
- Two years ago.
- What was his name?

01:20.681 --> 01:22.281
- Gabriel.

01:22.283 --> 01:23.849
You don't want this.

01:23.851 --> 01:27.152
- I'm a grown man.
I know what I want.

01:34.461 --> 01:37.596
- ♪ I was screaming
into the canyon ♪

01:37.598 --> 01:40.833
♪ at the moment of my death

01:40.835 --> 01:44.503
♪ the echo I created

01:44.505 --> 01:47.239
♪ outlasted my last breath

01:47.241 --> 01:50.843
♪ my voice,
it made an avalanche ♪

01:50.845 --> 01:53.645
♪ and buried a man
I never knew ♪

01:53.647 --> 01:55.647
♪ and when he died

01:55.649 --> 01:57.850
♪ his widowed bride
met your daddy ♪

01:57.852 --> 01:59.718
♪ and they made you

01:59.720 --> 02:02.121
♪ I have only one thing to do

02:02.123 --> 02:03.589
♪ and that's be the wave
that I am ♪

02:03.591 --> 02:06.525
♪ and then sink
back into the ocean ♪

02:06.527 --> 02:07.893
♪ I have only one thing to do

02:07.895 --> 02:09.628
♪ and that's be the wave
that I am ♪

02:09.630 --> 02:13.632
♪ and then sink
back into the ocean ♪

02:13.634 --> 02:15.200
♪ I have only one thing to do

02:15.202 --> 02:16.502
♪ and that's be the wave
that I am ♪

02:16.504 --> 02:19.271
♪ and then sink
back into the ocean ♪

02:19.273 --> 02:20.873
♪ sink back into the ocean

02:20.875 --> 02:22.207
♪ sing back into the o

02:22.209 --> 02:23.742
♪ sink back into the ocean

02:23.744 --> 02:25.344
♪ sink back into the o

02:25.346 --> 02:26.912
♪ sink back into the ocean

02:26.914 --> 02:29.615
♪ sink back
into the ocean ♪

02:29.617 --> 02:35.587
♪

03:05.685 --> 03:09.321
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:09.323 --> 03:12.658
- I'm gonna go surfing.
You want to come watch?

03:12.660 --> 03:16.562
- I couldn't sleep last night.

03:16.564 --> 03:20.299
- How come?

03:20.301 --> 03:23.335
- I'm gonna try
and get a few more hours.

03:25.738 --> 03:28.740
- Okay, stinko.

03:28.742 --> 03:31.743
- You're the stinko.

04:23.730 --> 04:25.731
- I forgot my wax.

04:59.032 --> 05:02.301
I love that dress on you.

06:32.058 --> 06:33.658
[car door closes]

06:39.465 --> 06:40.732
[knocking on door]

06:40.734 --> 06:42.934
- Okay.
[chuckles]

06:42.936 --> 06:44.569
Ah, perfect.

06:46.873 --> 06:49.007
[knocking on door]

06:50.777 --> 06:53.779
[mellow country rock]

06:53.781 --> 06:59.684
♪

06:59.686 --> 07:02.521
- ♪ come a little bit
closer ♪

07:02.523 --> 07:04.756
- Hey.
- Hey.

07:04.758 --> 07:07.426
♪

07:07.428 --> 07:09.895
- ♪ well, you got
a way of movin' ♪

07:09.897 --> 07:13.098
- So what do you think--
no, no, that's the kitchen.

07:13.100 --> 07:15.434
Bedroom.

07:15.436 --> 07:17.002
Oh--

07:19.972 --> 07:23.175
Stop looking at me!
[giggles]

07:23.177 --> 07:27.779
[moaning]

07:27.781 --> 07:29.681
No, stop, stop.

07:29.683 --> 07:31.716
Oh, stop.

07:46.833 --> 07:50.869
Oh, sh...
Sh...[laughs]

07:50.871 --> 07:53.472
- Who owns this place?

07:53.474 --> 07:57.075
Grateful dead?

07:57.077 --> 07:59.611
- My friend, phoebe.

07:59.613 --> 08:02.881
We grew up together.

08:02.883 --> 08:06.218
She's a folk musician and she
tours with different bands

08:06.220 --> 08:08.186
All over the world.

08:16.629 --> 08:20.999
- Did you ever
think about leaving?

08:21.001 --> 08:23.235
- Yeah.

08:23.237 --> 08:25.871
When I was younger
I wanted to be a doctor.

08:25.873 --> 08:29.641
- You did?

08:29.643 --> 08:32.978
- I thought about it.

08:32.980 --> 08:36.515
- What happened?

08:36.517 --> 08:38.583
- It was way too expensive.

08:38.585 --> 08:40.785
We didn't have enough money.

08:40.787 --> 08:43.255
I mean, I tried to get
a scholarship,

08:43.257 --> 08:45.857
But my boards
weren't good enough.

08:45.859 --> 08:48.727
We couldn't afford to pay
for all those extra classes,

08:48.729 --> 08:52.797
You know, that everyone
takes to help prepare?

08:52.799 --> 08:55.734
The system is rigged.

08:55.736 --> 08:58.036
- Yeah.

08:58.038 --> 08:59.938
I know it is.

09:08.147 --> 09:11.750
You think I grew up rich,
don't you?

09:11.752 --> 09:13.318
- What?

09:13.320 --> 09:18.757
- That's what
you're thinking right now.

09:18.759 --> 09:20.592
- Yeah.

09:24.897 --> 09:28.066
- My father drove a truck.

09:28.068 --> 09:30.168
My mom was a waitress.

09:31.904 --> 09:35.774
I went to college
on a swimming scholarship.

09:35.776 --> 09:39.311
- A waitress?
- Mm-hmm.

09:39.313 --> 09:43.648
- Wow.
A lot has changed for you.

09:43.650 --> 09:46.685
- Yeah, it has.

09:46.687 --> 09:48.186
[cell phone chimes]

09:48.188 --> 09:50.155
- Oh...

09:54.860 --> 09:56.328
Shit.

09:56.330 --> 09:58.196
It's my grandmother's
nursing home.

09:58.198 --> 10:00.198
They never call.

10:03.369 --> 10:07.072
Hi, it's alison bailey.

10:07.074 --> 10:08.673
Oh, hi, vera.

10:08.675 --> 10:12.344
Is everything okay?

10:12.346 --> 10:14.679
Oh...

10:14.681 --> 10:17.682
Right.

10:17.684 --> 10:20.285
No, no.
Don't change anything.

10:20.287 --> 10:22.354
She's just--no,
don't listen to her.

10:22.356 --> 10:25.156
I'll be there as soon as I can.

10:25.158 --> 10:28.827
Thank you so much.

10:28.829 --> 10:30.362
Fucking athena.

10:30.364 --> 10:32.697
She hasn't been there in years,

10:32.699 --> 10:36.001
And now she's trying to change
my grandmother's medication.

10:36.003 --> 10:37.969
She's probably broken up
with another boyfriend

10:37.971 --> 10:41.106
And to make herself feel
better she decides to come home

10:41.108 --> 10:44.709
And fuck everything up.

10:44.711 --> 10:47.379
My grandmother has alzheimer's.

10:47.381 --> 10:48.980
And when she's not on medication

10:48.982 --> 10:50.749
She's hysterical
because it's terrifying.

10:50.751 --> 10:53.752
But of course athena
doesn't care about that.

10:53.754 --> 10:55.120
- Who's athena?

10:55.122 --> 10:57.122
- My mother.

10:59.125 --> 11:03.261
Look, I have to go.

11:03.263 --> 11:05.063
- Can I see you later?

11:05.065 --> 11:08.867
- I have to work.

11:08.869 --> 11:10.402
Maybe after my shift?

11:10.404 --> 11:12.270
5:30?

11:12.272 --> 11:14.339
- Yeah, I'll take that.

11:23.282 --> 11:26.451
- Oh, god,
you're so hot.

11:26.453 --> 11:29.688
- Which part do you like best?

11:31.424 --> 11:32.857
- Ow.

11:34.427 --> 11:36.027
Later?

11:36.029 --> 11:39.097
- Okay.
- Okay, bye.

12:10.863 --> 12:12.731
Hey, shandy.
- How are you, sweetie?

12:12.733 --> 12:15.100
- I'm good.
- You look good, girl.

12:15.102 --> 12:16.468
- Thanks.

12:16.470 --> 12:17.802
Hey, james.

12:27.813 --> 12:31.449
- I felt you...
Coming down the hall.

12:33.986 --> 12:36.287
Oh, god.

12:40.960 --> 12:42.861
- Well, I had no clue
you were coming.

12:42.863 --> 12:44.996
- Well, it was an impulse visit.

12:44.998 --> 12:47.165
I sensed that my mother
needed me.

12:47.167 --> 12:49.367
And of course
I always want to see you.

12:49.369 --> 12:51.970
Oh, god.
You look so pretty.

12:51.972 --> 12:53.505
[laughs]

12:53.507 --> 12:55.774
- What's going on?

12:55.776 --> 12:58.143
- Well, grandma's
not doing well at all.

12:58.145 --> 13:00.445
I could feel it all the way
in jaipur.

13:00.447 --> 13:03.381
And then when I got here
she was just so out of it.

13:03.383 --> 13:05.850
They overmedicate them so they
don't have to deal with them,

13:05.852 --> 13:07.318
You know.
- No, she's not overmedicated.

13:07.320 --> 13:09.020
- Sweetie,
she didn't even recognize me.

13:09.022 --> 13:10.989
- Well, she was fine
when I was here last week.

13:10.991 --> 13:13.792
- Do you only come once a week?

13:24.537 --> 13:27.172
Hi, mommy.

13:27.174 --> 13:29.541
See?

13:29.543 --> 13:31.543
- Oh, alison.

13:31.545 --> 13:33.444
- I brought you some peaches
from cherry's orchard.

13:33.446 --> 13:36.948
- Ah, thank you, dear.

13:36.950 --> 13:39.918
I love them.

13:39.920 --> 13:42.887
Tell me about this show.

13:42.889 --> 13:44.155
These people are trapped
together.

13:44.157 --> 13:45.557
Are they related?

13:45.559 --> 13:48.426
- Uh...
- It's garbage, mom.

13:48.428 --> 13:51.029
It's about people
wanting to be famous.

13:51.031 --> 13:53.298
- Is this woman
a friend of yours?

13:53.300 --> 13:56.467
She was here earlier.

13:56.469 --> 13:58.570
- It's athena, your daughter.

13:58.572 --> 14:00.905
- Mama?

14:00.907 --> 14:03.508
- I had a daughter, shelly.

14:03.510 --> 14:06.311
- I changed it, mom.
Remember?

14:06.313 --> 14:08.479
- She was very bright.

14:08.481 --> 14:10.048
She's a nurse now.

14:10.050 --> 14:11.482
- I'm your daughter.

14:11.484 --> 14:13.084
My name used to be shelly.

14:13.086 --> 14:15.386
I changed it many years ago.

14:15.388 --> 14:18.323
I'm not a nurse
but I am a healer.

14:18.325 --> 14:23.094
I practice reiki and other forms
of energy work.

14:23.096 --> 14:24.529
- Don't you make fun of me.

14:24.531 --> 14:26.064
- No, I'm not--

14:26.066 --> 14:28.199
- It was me
who went to nursing school.

14:28.201 --> 14:29.634
You were right, grandma.

14:29.636 --> 14:31.336
- Oh, yeah.
You studied so hard.

14:31.338 --> 14:34.072
You were always
such a good student.

14:37.209 --> 14:40.144
Now, tell me something
about yourself, dear.

14:43.215 --> 14:47.385
- Well, I'm a senior teacher

14:47.387 --> 14:49.254
At the omega institute

14:49.256 --> 14:53.491
For holistic studies and healing
and spiritual development.

14:53.493 --> 14:56.494
And my private practice
is flourishing.

14:56.496 --> 15:01.132
And I do workshops and trainings
all over the world.

15:01.134 --> 15:02.567
- Is sal here with you?

15:02.569 --> 15:05.270
- No, we're no longer
traveling together.

15:05.272 --> 15:07.405
- Oh, you mean you broke up?

15:07.407 --> 15:10.508
- We came to the end
of our story.

15:10.510 --> 15:13.044
- Hi, joan.

15:13.046 --> 15:15.113
It's time to take your pills.

15:15.115 --> 15:18.416
- Oh, god. Look how much
they're giving her.

15:18.418 --> 15:19.918
- What is it? What's wrong?

15:19.920 --> 15:21.386
- It's too many drugs, mom.

15:21.388 --> 15:23.054
- No, they're trying
to poison me again.

15:23.056 --> 15:24.989
- No, no,
no one's gonna hurt you.

15:24.991 --> 15:26.691
They love you here.

15:26.693 --> 15:31.462
And I'd never let anyone give
you the wrong medicine, okay?

15:35.167 --> 15:37.068
Here.

15:39.138 --> 15:41.606
Two of them slow the progression
of her cognitive impairment.

15:41.608 --> 15:44.142
One is for anxiety and one
is an anti-depressant,

15:44.144 --> 15:45.410
'cause frankly it's depressing

15:45.412 --> 15:47.178
To be losing your mind
and dying.

15:47.180 --> 15:48.680
- Please don't talk to me
like I'm an idiot.

15:48.682 --> 15:50.415
I am a highly trained
professional.

15:50.417 --> 15:52.550
The a.M.A. Is not god.

15:52.552 --> 15:55.186
There are myriad alternative
therapies for all those things.

15:55.188 --> 15:56.554
Acupuncture, biofeedback...
- Athena,

15:56.556 --> 15:58.356
Those are bullshit therapies...
- Homeopathy--

15:58.358 --> 16:00.959
- That offer questionable
relief to minor conditions.

16:00.961 --> 16:02.694
- I wish you would just
call me mom.

16:02.696 --> 16:05.163
- And grandma seems worse
because she is worse.

16:05.165 --> 16:07.198
It gets worse,
and she needs medication.

16:07.200 --> 16:09.434
- Why are you getting upset?

16:09.436 --> 16:11.469
- Because you're upsetting her.

16:11.471 --> 16:14.439
- I'm worried this is too much
for you being her proxy.

16:14.441 --> 16:17.442
Why don't you let me take over
her health decisions, sweetie?

16:17.444 --> 16:19.243
- Are you kidding me?

16:19.245 --> 16:20.712
You have to be here.

16:20.714 --> 16:22.447
- I'll be here more.
I will.

16:22.449 --> 16:24.115
- No, you won't.
[elevator bell dings]

16:39.631 --> 16:41.599
- Honey, let me
take you to dinner tonight.

16:41.601 --> 16:43.401
Just the two of us.

16:43.403 --> 16:45.503
- No, I'm having dinner
at the lockharts' tonight.

16:45.505 --> 16:47.739
- Oh, well.

16:47.741 --> 16:51.075
- Well, you could come but I
know how much you love cherry.

16:51.077 --> 16:53.511
- How about a drink, then?
After work.

16:53.513 --> 16:55.246
- I can't.
- Why?

16:55.248 --> 16:58.383
- I have to check on a house
I'm taking care of.

16:58.385 --> 16:59.484
- Whose house?

16:59.486 --> 17:00.651
- Phoebe's!

17:00.653 --> 17:03.254
[whispers]
god, who cares? Jesus.

17:03.256 --> 17:05.723
[engine turns]

17:17.169 --> 17:18.770
No.
Are you going back in?

17:18.772 --> 17:22.240
- Yes.
I want to be with my mother.

17:22.242 --> 17:25.243
- Can you please try
not to agitate her?

17:29.515 --> 17:30.782
Oh, shit.

17:36.655 --> 17:38.656
Fuck, come on.

17:42.694 --> 17:44.395
- Don't rush.

17:44.397 --> 17:45.797
Couldn't be slower.

17:45.799 --> 17:48.733
- Good.
Thanks for covering for me.

17:48.735 --> 17:51.536
- Mm-hmm.

17:51.538 --> 17:54.806
- Guess who showed up
like a nasty cold sore?

17:54.808 --> 17:57.141
- Athena?
- You got it.

17:57.143 --> 17:59.844
- I'm sorry.
Was there drama?

17:59.846 --> 18:01.179
- Morning, sunshine.

18:01.181 --> 18:03.848
- Not so loud, bailey.

18:03.850 --> 18:07.585
Oh, hey, can I, uh,
borrow your phone?

18:07.587 --> 18:09.087
Mine's dead.

18:09.089 --> 18:11.422
- Didn't make it home
last night?

18:11.424 --> 18:14.158
- Just pass me the device.

18:14.160 --> 18:16.327
- Why can't you
use the house phone?

18:16.329 --> 18:18.096
- Because your brother-in-law
owes me a delivery

18:18.098 --> 18:19.697
And I want to send him
a reminder, bailey.

18:19.699 --> 18:22.667
And I believe
you have the number.

18:25.370 --> 18:29.173
- I'll do it for you.

18:29.175 --> 18:31.309
- What are you saying?

18:31.311 --> 18:35.179
- I'm saying
you want to see him.

18:35.181 --> 18:37.582
Done.

18:37.584 --> 18:38.850
- Thanks.

18:38.852 --> 18:41.853
[music plays in background]

18:41.855 --> 18:45.356
♪

18:45.358 --> 18:51.262
Say, uh...You still
watching phoebe cutler's house?

18:51.264 --> 18:54.265
- Yeah, why?

18:56.201 --> 18:58.169
- No reason.

19:19.892 --> 19:22.360
- It does. It's like chip
all over again.

19:22.362 --> 19:24.495
- You guys, you ready to order?

19:24.497 --> 19:28.900
- Yeah, um...
We'll get...

19:28.902 --> 19:30.568
What are you getting?

19:30.570 --> 19:33.504
- Um...
- Don't know?

19:33.506 --> 19:35.239
- Dunno, between the chicken
fingers and the salad.

19:35.241 --> 19:36.807
[low chatter]

19:36.809 --> 19:38.910
- Can I maybe get
the seafood nachos

19:38.912 --> 19:42.780
But without the melted
cheddar cheese?

19:42.782 --> 19:44.382
- Uh, yeah.

19:44.384 --> 19:45.583
- Maybe water. I don't know.

19:45.585 --> 19:47.318
Should I just
get the chicken fingers?

19:47.320 --> 19:48.719
- I say go for it.

19:48.721 --> 19:51.923
- I don't know.
Are they, like, really breaded?

19:51.925 --> 19:53.591
- Yes, they are.

19:56.828 --> 20:00.198
[blues plays in background]

20:00.200 --> 20:01.866
- Later.

20:13.712 --> 20:15.213
- Jane, jane? You're cut.

20:15.215 --> 20:17.415
Go have fun.

20:17.417 --> 20:19.317
What? Is there a problem?

20:19.319 --> 20:21.619
- She's still got two tables
left. I'm empty.

20:21.621 --> 20:25.556
- Yeah, you were late.
She covered for you.

20:25.558 --> 20:26.958
- How do you know that?

20:26.960 --> 20:28.326
- I didn't say anything.

20:28.328 --> 20:29.994
- Took an educated guess,
bailey,

20:29.996 --> 20:31.862
And you just
confirmed it for me.

20:31.864 --> 20:34.565
Man, it's so lonely being
smarter than everyone else.

20:34.567 --> 20:36.334
[chuckles]

20:36.336 --> 20:38.636
What? Oh, you got somewhere else
you'd rather be?

20:38.638 --> 20:39.837
- Yeah, anywhere but here.

20:39.839 --> 20:43.374
- Ah, see now, that hurts me.

20:48.313 --> 20:49.914
Have a good one.

20:50.916 --> 20:52.650
- Come on...

20:57.589 --> 21:00.858
- So, oscar had a relationship
with the victim?

21:00.860 --> 21:04.395
- Yeah, they were friends.

21:04.397 --> 21:09.467
- And scotty stopped by that day
because...

21:09.469 --> 21:13.004
- I honestly don't know,
detective.

